messages.subject: MIL to DH
messages.msgSnippet: MIL to DH: You are a wonderful person with qualities I admire. I probably forced you to showcase those qualities, because I only wanted you to show me the
messages.messageBody:
MIL to DH: "You are a wonderful person with qualities I admire. I probably forced you to showcase those qualities, because I only wanted you to show me the ones I liked. You'd get the message I didn't love you if you showed me anything else. It's tiring being around people who are free to be who they are; I was taught it's wrong to be loud, or angry, or to have any strong feelings whatsoever. I wish everyone would conform to what I'm comfortable with."

(just guessing, obviously)

Caren

messages.messageBody:
Something has been bothering for several months. I have been trying to
roll what someone said over and over in my head searching for a nice
way to hear it. I will refrain from saying what I am thinking and try
to be open to others interprtations.

MIL to my DH, "it's too bad none of your children got your disposition."

Thanks for any insight.
Faith


Sent from my iPhone
